  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Bolded scores denote the best performance with respect to the task.",
    "DRG-LLaMA outperformed ClinicalBERT and CAML across all evaluation metrics, with better performance in more frequent DRGs.",
    "DRG denotes diagnostis-related group, AUC denotes area under the receiver operating characteristic curve, and ACC denotes accuracy.",
    "In the two-label approach, we first dissect each DRG into two distinct components: a base DRG label and a CC/MCC label (denoting complication or comorbidity / major complication or comorbidity).",
    "This dissection process was based on the composition delineated within the MS-DRG v34.0 definitions manual 8."
  ],
